headline: 3 Reasons to Avoid JCI and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Since July 2020, the S&P 500 has delivered a total return of 97.3%. But one standout stock has more than doubled the market - over the past five years, Johnson Controls has surged 218% to $106.12 per share. Its momentum hasn’t stopped as it’s also gained 34.9% in the last six months thanks to its solid quarterly results, beating the S&P by 28.1%.
